142
00:10:51,040 --> 00:10:51,620
(gulping)

143
00:10:53,140 --> 00:10:56,480
- So, now then, go on and finish me off.

144
00:10:58,460 --> 00:10:59,520
- Let's run away.

145
00:11:01,570 --> 00:11:03,300
I want you to run away with me.

146
00:11:06,840 --> 00:11:07,420
(laughing)

147
00:11:08,200 --> 00:11:09,620
- Where'd you come up with that idea?

148
00:11:10,160 --> 00:11:11,860
Me, run away with you?

149
00:11:12,060 --> 00:11:13,220
You're kidding, right?

150
00:11:14,560 --> 00:11:16,140
Refresh my memory.

151
00:11:16,540 --> 00:11:18,840
When did you and I become so close?

152
00:11:18,840 --> 00:11:23,580
I can't do it. I can't kill people anymore.

153
00:11:23,820 --> 00:11:25,140
You can't kill people?

154
00:11:25,560 --> 00:11:29,600
Well, I bet that you can still kill a devil, because that's what I am!

155
00:11:29,820 --> 00:11:33,560
You think I bought you that new suit and necktie because I like you?

156
00:11:33,840 --> 00:11:36,540
Those are the same clothes that Kenzo used to wear!

157
00:11:36,940 --> 00:11:40,040
Don't you get it? I was just turning you into Kenzo Tenma!

158
00:11:40,360 --> 00:11:41,520
Just kill me already!

159
00:11:45,960 --> 00:12:01,000
Come on! Do it! Quick! Kill me! Quickly! Kill me quickly, you big jerk. If you don't kill

160
00:12:01,000 --> 00:12:05,480
Tell me quickly, they'll come to kill you too.

161
00:12:18,960 --> 00:12:21,620
Kill the devil, huh?

162
00:12:28,280 --> 00:12:30,800
Come on, Mom! Wake up!

163
00:12:31,020 --> 00:12:35,080
It's all right. After a nap, I'll start sobering up.

164
00:12:35,640 --> 00:12:38,940
Well, you can't nap now! You'll die if you go to sleep here!

165
00:12:39,120 --> 00:12:41,680
I'll be fine. Just leave me here so I can rest.

166
00:13:04,560 --> 00:13:07,360
(owl hooting)

167
00:13:34,380 --> 00:13:36,140
You look depressed today.

168
00:13:36,640 --> 00:13:37,680
What do you mean, Robbie?

169
00:13:37,740 --> 00:13:38,960
I always look like this.

170
00:13:39,700 --> 00:13:42,280
So tell me, has anybody come around here looking for me today?

171
00:13:42,620 --> 00:13:48,040
Well, nobody knew, but that Japanese doctor guy from yesterday left you this.

172
00:13:50,440 --> 00:13:53,520
The Hellbrow Hotel, room number 205.

173
00:13:53,520 --> 00:13:56,160
He said to call him if anything happened.

174
00:13:56,980 --> 00:13:58,680
So, what'll you have, Martin?

175
00:13:58,880 --> 00:14:00,000
Do you want your usual?

176
00:14:00,820 --> 00:14:01,640
Not today.

177
00:14:02,640 --> 00:14:04,420
Fill my stomach with your lousy burgers,

178
00:14:04,580 --> 00:14:06,060
and I won't feel like going anywhere.

179
00:14:06,660 --> 00:14:08,360
Oh, yeah? Where are you going?

180
00:14:09,320 --> 00:14:10,420
Another party.

181
00:14:11,080 --> 00:14:11,240
[Chuckles]

182
00:14:13,500 --> 00:14:14,620
It's amazing.

183
00:14:15,580 --> 00:14:18,080
I can go anywhere if I have a necktie.

184
00:14:19,020 --> 00:14:21,500
Just a single little necktie.

185
00:14:32,980 --> 00:14:41,260
Jackpot. So, he's the devil? After shaking hands with what seemed like countless people,

186
00:14:41,260 --> 00:14:45,460
Well, he left the party alone.

187
